This panel has a ~KGoto~E editor at the top which provides a fast and
easy way to navigate to a particular entry using the keyboard.
(See [Finding Entries xix_tu_nav.html] for other techniques.)
''</td></tr></table>''
''<table bgcolor="lightyellow"><tr><td>''
Press ~KCtrl+T~E or click the editor to give it the focus, then type in
the first few letters of the term for the entry you want to visit. For
small indexes, two or three letters should be sufficient, while larger
indexes may need three or four letters. This should get you to the entry
you want, or within easy reach of it, either by clicking it, or by
pressing ~KTab~E (or ~KAlt+I~E), then ~KDown~E or ~KUp~E arrow until you
reach the right entry.
''</td></tr></table>''

The current entry is shown highlighted with a yellow background and a
solid black bullet. The current entry is also shown in the
[Main Window Entry Panel xix_ref_panel_entry.html], where it can be
edited.

It is possible to circle an entry using the
[Entry→Circle action xix_ref_act_y_circ.html].
A circled entry that is //also// the current entry is shown with a green
background and with a hollow bullet with a dot in it. A circled entry
that is not the current entry is shown with a cyan background and a
hollow bullet. When the current and circled entries are different it is
possible to do actions involving both: for example, making a cross-reference
from the current to the circled entry, or moving the current entry to be
a subentry of the circled entry.

